1. Definitions

"Software" means the NewBedWars source code, compiled binaries, resource
files, configuration templates, and any files distributed with this
repository.

"Licensor" means the copyright holder of the Software.

"External Integration" means a separate and independent work that interacts
with the Software without modifying the Software itself. Examples include:

- configuration changes made through supported config files
- separate plugins or addons that use public APIs, commands, events or
  integration points
- scripts, panels, launchers or deployment tools that install, manage or
  communicate with the Software from the outside

"Modification" means any direct change to the Software itself, including but
not limited to editing, patching, decompiling for alteration, recompiling a
changed version, merging code into the Software, altering packaged classes,
changing bundled resources, or distributing a derivative work based on the
Software.

