- distribute unmodified copies of the Software, provided this license and all
  copyright notices remain intact
- create and use External Integrations

3. Prohibited Actions

You may not, without prior written permission from the Licensor:

- modify the Software
- create or distribute modified source code
- create or distribute modified binaries or patched jar files
- publish forks whose purpose is to distribute a modified version of the
  Software
- remove, hide or alter copyright, authorship or license notices
- sublicense the Software under different terms

4. Clarification About External Integrations

External Integrations are allowed as long as they remain separate works and do
not include or distribute a modified version of the Software.

For clarity, the following are allowed:

- creating a plugin that hooks into supported behavior from outside
- changing server files, startup scripts or configs that the Software already
  supports
- building dashboards, wrappers or automation around the Software

The following are not allowed without written permission:

- editing the source code and compiling your own version
- unpacking or patching the jar to change behavior
- distributing a customized build
- copying parts of the source into another project in modified form

